TopicTitle: Can't find part from K&K Planetary Base Systems in Seti-CTT

Articles.Content: Hi all! I can't seem to find the part "K&K Bi-coupler" from Planety Base Systems mod in the Seti-CTT, no matter how hard i try. Can someone give me a hint on the node pls before my eyeballs pop out? Thx.
The dev said that it was compatible, I actually was the one who asked for a support check, but look in the config of the bicoupler or make a modulemanager config to change it.

I Believe Nils already said this was a bug and how to fix it until he puts out his next release.

http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/127413-WIP-1-0-4-Kerbal-Planetary-Base-Systems-v0-2-6-Update-8-10-2015?p=2241249&viewfull=1#post2241249

I Believe Nils already said this was a bug and how to fix it until he puts out his next release.

http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/127413-WIP-1-0-4-Kerbal-Planetary-Base-Systems-v0-2-6-Update-8-10-2015?p=2241249&viewfull=1#post2241249

JPLRepo is right ;-)

I accidentally have added some ';' in the config file for (SETI)CTT. To be precise in the configs/KPBS_MM_CTT file. Just remove all ';' you find there and the parts should be available again.

The fix for it will be in the next update.
